---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = '2026-04-27';
---

<BaseLayout
	title="Privacy Policy"
	description="The Thirsty Pig privacy policy — what (little) data this site handles."
>
	<section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
		<h1 class="font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-ink mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
		<p class="text-stone mb-8 text-sm">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

		<div class="prose max-w-none">
			<h2>The short version</h2>
			<p>
				The Thirsty Pig is a personal food blog. It does not collect, store, or
				share personal information about you. There are no analytics, no email
				signups, no cookies that identify you, and no third-party trackers.
			</p>

			<h2>What's actually stored</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<strong>A theme preference cookie</strong> &mdash; If you toggle dark mode,
					your browser stores your choice locally so the site remembers next visit.
					This is held in <code>localStorage</code> on your device. It is not sent
					to any server. Clearing your browser data removes it.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Standard server logs</strong> &mdash; The site is hosted on
					<a href="https://vercel.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Vercel</a>,
					which keeps short-term operational logs (IP, user agent, requested URL)
					for caching and abuse prevention. These are governed by
					<a href="https://vercel.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
						Vercel's privacy policy
					</a>.
				</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>What this site does NOT do</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>No Google Analytics, no Meta Pixel, no other behavioural trackers.</li>
				<li>No email/newsletter signup forms.</li>
				<li>No advertising network. No tracking pixels.</li>
				<li>No selling, sharing, or transferring of any user data to third parties.</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Embedded content</h2>
			<p>
				Some posts may embed images or videos hosted on third-party services
				(Instagram, YouTube, Vimeo). Those services may set their own cookies
				when their content loads. If you don't visit those services directly
				from this site, no information about you is sent to them by The Thirsty
				Pig itself.
			</p>

			<h2>Sources of content</h2>
			<p>
				Posts on this site come from three places: the original blog
				(2007&ndash;2017, recovered from the Internet Archive), an Instagram data
				export, and an automated sync from the Thirsty Pig Facebook Page. None of
				those pipelines collect data <em>about visitors</em>; they only import
				the author's own posts.
			</p>

			<h2>Contact</h2>
			<p>
				Questions about this policy? Reach out via
				<a href="https://instagram.com/thirstypig" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
					@thirstypig on Instagram
				</a>.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>
